description: This file defines the 'Note' data model for the notes manager application, utilizing Python's dataclasses to represent notes with attributes and a static method to instantiate objects from database rows.

classes.name: Note
classes.description: A data class representing a note with attributes such as id, title, content, created_at, and updated_at, including a static method to instantiate from a database row.

methods.name: 'Note' from_row(row: dict)
methods.description: Creates a Note instance from a database row dictionary.
